    <note>Zhao(1) Wenyu [24378] According to Su(1) Song [8116], who was the nephew of Wenyu's son-in-law, Su(1) Jie(2) [11617] (Song's father's younger cousin), Wenyu used being son of a state council member to establish his family branch of the lineage (qijia) by entering the civil service. It is possible that son-in-laws, Shen(2) Kui and Shen(2) Mai (not in dataset) are cousins of Shen(2) Liao [1453] and Shen(2) Gou [1449], who have the same generational names and are chronological contemporaries, but there is no documentary evidence to support this hypothesis. Su Song, WJ, 58.5b-10b. CBD, 4, 3584.</note>
